30/05/2003
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The National Anti-Corruption Prosecution Office arrested 12 policemen in Bucharest on Wednesday (28 May) over suspected links to organised crime.
They allegedly acted as guards during attacks on the Petrotrans oil pipeline, demanding significant amounts of protection money.
If convicted, they could face four to 20 years in prison.
Afterwards, the Bucharest Police Department issued a press release confirming zero tolerance for staff members that violate the law.
(Rompres, Nine o'Clock - 30/05/03)
